00:27:27,645 --> 00:27:29,147
(Chief Referee) Defendant’s Agent

489
00:27:29,647 --> 00:27:33,151
Please explain the purpose of the proof in an easy-to-understand manner.

490
00:27:33,652 --> 00:27:35,528
To clarify the purpose...

491
00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:41,785
Witness Kazuteru Kumakura for the plaintiff⸺

492
00:27:41,868 --> 00:27:45,538
I request that I be re-examined as a witness for the defendant.

493
00:27:50,543 --> 00:27:52,837
It's finally time to go on the offensive.

494
00:27:54,756 --> 00:27:58,802
(Kazuki) “Speak the truth according to your sworn conscience⸺”

495
00:27:59,386 --> 00:28:05,350
“I promise not to hide anything or lie.”

496
00:28:16,611 --> 00:28:21,324
(Tatsumi) The first player, 3 squares, is the next 24 horses, 5 and 1 dragon is tough⸺

497
00:28:21,408 --> 00:28:24,411
At first glance, the first player appears to be winning.

498
00:28:26,663 --> 00:28:28,707
I will show you proof No. 5

499
00:28:28,790 --> 00:28:30,417
This is from Gankoan⸺

500
00:28:30,500 --> 00:28:33,253
This is a recipe submitted to Queen Marche

501
00:28:34,629 --> 00:28:36,798
Could you please read this part?

502
00:28:40,719 --> 00:28:45,432
“When making gyuhi, pay attention to the room temperature and humidity⸺”

503
00:28:45,515 --> 00:28:48,852
“Knead while checking the hardness of the dough every 20 minutes”

504
00:28:48,935 --> 00:28:51,146
“It takes 3 to 4 hours.”

505
00:28:51,229 --> 00:28:57,026
(Tatsumi) At Ganko-an, gyuhi takes at least 3 hours at a low temperature⸺

506
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:59,821
Craftsmen work diligently to create the product.

507
00:28:59,904 --> 00:29:01,114
I agree?

508
00:29:01,823 --> 00:29:02,699
yes

509
00:29:03,491 --> 00:29:04,993
 (Tatsumi) First move 5 Ichiryu (Ryu)

510
00:29:05,076 --> 00:29:07,787
...But the Ittetsu Mochi that Misuzu-san made is⸺

511
00:29:07,871 --> 00:29:10,707
Process that originally required more than 3 hours⸺

512
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:14,544
It was made in a pressure cooker in just 30 minutes.

513
00:29:14,627 --> 00:29:18,339
It had the same taste as Queen Marche's Ittetsu Mochi.

514
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:21,468
Please explain what this means

515
00:29:23,595 --> 00:29:25,472
Back hand 2 ounces

516
00:29:28,808 --> 00:29:30,685
This is an exquisite technique

517
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:33,563
(Kasumi) Ryumi taught me the game record in advance.

518
00:29:33,646 --> 00:29:35,315
Maybe Ryumi⸺

519
00:29:35,398 --> 00:29:38,485
Two squares is just subtracted.

520
00:29:38,568 --> 00:29:40,361
Um... this horn can be made, right?

521
00:29:40,445 --> 00:29:43,823
(Kasumi) No, I don't think so.

522
00:29:43,907 --> 00:29:45,325
(Kaga) Don't make me testify.

523
00:29:46,409 --> 00:29:49,788
This is a leading questioning of a defendant's attorney who has an objection.

524
00:29:49,871 --> 00:29:51,706
(Presiding Judge) Please continue.

525
00:29:53,583 --> 00:29:56,753
Mr. Kazuki, could you please answer?

526
00:29:58,838 --> 00:30:02,884
How much time do you have to prepare the gyuhi for Queen Marche’s Ittetsu Mochi?

527
00:30:02,967 --> 00:30:06,054
How many minutes was it actually?

528
00:30:13,853 --> 00:30:16,815
(Kazuteru) Shorten the time to prepare gyuhi?

529
00:30:16,898 --> 00:30:19,234
(Kaga) I can't believe someone spends three hours there!

530
00:30:19,317 --> 00:30:20,610
Taipa is too bad

531
00:30:20,693 --> 00:30:22,779
...However, in the recipe of Gankoan

532
00:30:22,862 --> 00:30:27,450
Using a steamer can shorten the gyuhi process to 30 minutes.

533
00:30:28,117 --> 00:30:30,036
The appearance and taste remain the same⸺

534
00:30:30,119 --> 00:30:31,913
No need to run out of stock

535
00:30:34,123 --> 00:30:36,334
Dad, you want to surpass me, right?

536
00:30:54,894 --> 00:30:57,438
Your father is truly an amazing confectionery craftsman.

537
00:30:57,522 --> 00:30:58,690
I think too

538
00:31:00,316 --> 00:31:04,946
I'm so worried about how my son compares himself to you.

539
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:11,369
Such a father⸺

540
00:31:11,452 --> 00:31:13,830
I love the taste that I have been particular about for many years⸺

541
00:31:13,913 --> 00:31:16,833
Because of the mother who continued to support the shop⸺

542
00:31:16,916 --> 00:31:19,836
I was able to notice a slight difference in taste.

543
00:31:21,504 --> 00:31:22,714
Huh?

544
00:31:23,673 --> 00:31:27,051
Please answer honestly for both of us.

545
00:31:28,469 --> 00:31:31,639
Time to prepare Queen Marche’s gyuhi⸺

546
00:31:32,765 --> 00:31:33,641
How many minutes?

547
00:31:54,495 --> 00:31:57,749
Well… 30 minutes…

548
00:32:01,127 --> 00:32:05,423
30 minutes in a steamer

549
00:32:12,347 --> 00:32:14,599
(Tatsumi) 2 diagonal failure (Nara)

550
00:32:19,228 --> 00:32:20,396
Mr. Kazuki

551
00:32:21,481 --> 00:32:24,359
The time spent on gyuhi has been significantly reduced⸺

552
00:32:25,026 --> 00:32:26,736
Queen Marche’s Ittetsu Mochi is⸺

553
00:32:26,819 --> 00:32:30,406
Even if it's a fake that wasn't made properly⸺

554
00:32:30,907 --> 00:32:31,991
There's no doubt about it, right?

555
00:32:39,499 --> 00:32:41,834
That's all for this question.

556
00:32:46,089 --> 00:32:51,469
The plaintiff would like to offer a settlement to the defendant.

557
00:32:52,804 --> 00:32:55,682
(Kasumi) Conceded the first move. What a wonderful come-from-behind victory.

558
00:32:55,765 --> 00:32:58,267
(Presiding Judge) What are the intentions of the defendant's attorney?

559
00:32:58,768 --> 00:33:00,561
I will be happy to comply

560
00:33:06,067 --> 00:33:09,320
To be carried away by emotion and forget about business?

561
00:33:09,404 --> 00:33:11,781
I'm so disappointed in you.

562
00:33:17,453 --> 00:33:20,707
I would like you to respond to the media while considering the settlement proposal.

563
00:33:20,790 --> 00:33:21,874
(Ayame) Yes

564
00:33:32,093 --> 00:33:34,929
I have a story that I would like everyone to hear.

565
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:38,099
Huh? Even though the trial is over?

566
00:33:38,683 --> 00:33:40,560
There is still some impressions left

567
00:33:44,105 --> 00:33:48,234
(Tatsumi) Ittetsu mochi made with gyuhi in a short time

568
00:33:48,901 --> 00:33:53,489
In fact, wasn't Mr. Kumakura himself the one who created it some time ago?

569
00:33:57,118 --> 00:34:00,413
5 years ago, Yuzu collapsed⸺

570
00:34:00,496 --> 00:34:02,039
When you were hospitalized...

571
00:34:03,708 --> 00:34:05,918
(Kazuki) Where and what were you doing until this hour?

572
00:34:06,002 --> 00:34:08,296
I'm sure he was making sweets.

573
00:34:08,796 --> 00:34:12,133
(Tatsumi) Mr. Kumakura is exactly as he said⸺

574
00:34:12,633 --> 00:34:15,678
Yuzu-san’s favorite Ittetsu mochi⸺

575
00:34:15,762 --> 00:34:18,097
You worked really hard to make it, right?

576
00:34:19,599 --> 00:34:23,644
I want to deliver it to Yuzu-san as soon as possible.

577
00:34:24,145 --> 00:34:28,566
With that single-mindedness, the work that would normally take more than 3 hours⸺

578
00:34:28,649 --> 00:34:33,488
I finished it in a short time using a pressure cooker and took it to the hospital room.

579
00:34:35,198 --> 00:34:38,493
(Yuzu) Oh no, it was you?

580
00:34:38,993 --> 00:34:43,748
I ate it and thought it tasted slightly different.

581
00:34:44,332 --> 00:34:49,295
Thanks to Yuzu-san's tongue, I understood everything.

582
00:34:51,631 --> 00:34:54,383
If that's the case, then why don't you just say that then?

583
00:34:56,677 --> 00:34:59,138
My father always acts like a craftsman⸺

584
00:34:59,931 --> 00:35:01,808
Because I don't say anything important

585
00:35:03,434 --> 00:35:07,772
Kazuki-san is also the one who hides his true feelings and doesn't say anything.

586
00:35:07,855 --> 00:35:08,689
Huh?

587
00:35:11,442 --> 00:35:17,198
This game... Ah... I'm in the middle of a trial.

588
00:35:17,698 --> 00:35:21,369
In other words, our trick is⸺

589
00:35:21,452 --> 00:35:26,791
This two squares are not completed.

590
00:35:26,874 --> 00:35:31,045
If the angle is formed⸺

591
00:35:31,128 --> 00:35:33,548
We, who were on the draw, were stuck with 19 moves⸺

592
00:35:33,631 --> 00:35:35,258
I lost

593
00:35:35,341 --> 00:35:38,970
...But because the angle didn't form⸺

594
00:35:39,053 --> 00:35:41,764
After that, the flow changed and the player conceded the first move⸺

595
00:35:41,848 --> 00:35:43,641
I was able to push

596
00:35:45,309 --> 00:35:47,270
 (sound pointing to piece)

597
00:35:52,942 --> 00:35:54,694
This is the end

598
00:35:54,777 --> 00:35:57,155
(Torataro) According to Dr. Ryumi⸺

599
00:35:57,238 --> 00:36:00,950
Gankoan won in this trial⸺

600
00:36:01,993 --> 00:36:06,038
Because the piece that was supposed to become normal didn't happen.

601
00:36:07,248 --> 00:36:10,418
I won because I didn't succeed

602
00:36:11,586 --> 00:36:15,339
Truly cut ties with Gankoan and Japanese sweets⸺

603
00:36:15,423 --> 00:36:18,050
If you had chosen the path to becoming rich⸺

604
00:36:18,885 --> 00:36:24,181
He could have refused to testify about his time at Gyuhi.

605
00:36:24,265 --> 00:36:28,269
However, Mr. Kazuki did not dare to become successful⸺

606
00:36:28,352 --> 00:36:30,605
You spoke honestly.

607
00:36:34,650 --> 00:36:39,197
Kazuki's heart is still in this Gankoan.

608
00:36:40,823 --> 00:36:42,283
Believe so⸺

609
00:36:44,243 --> 00:36:46,245
I bet on this one move

610
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:52,001
My brother's heart is still with me...

611
00:36:53,377 --> 00:36:55,546
(Yuzu) As expected.

612
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:59,634
Kazuki really loves our sweets.

613
00:36:59,717 --> 00:37:01,677
...Or rather, they're eating our sweets⸺

614
00:37:01,761 --> 00:37:04,347
There's nothing more important than seeing the smiles on our customers' faces.

615
00:37:05,723 --> 00:37:09,769
I've always wanted more people to eat it⸺

616
00:37:09,852 --> 00:37:12,146
That's what I said every time something happened.

617
00:37:12,813 --> 00:37:16,400
(Misuzu) Maybe that's why you can buy ittetsu mochi by mail order?

618
00:37:20,029 --> 00:37:21,572
For mail order⸺

619
00:37:22,531 --> 00:37:27,078
Our taste can be delivered anywhere in the country

620
00:37:30,748 --> 00:37:34,669
It's a nouveau riche or it's Ayumu⸺

621
00:37:35,586 --> 00:37:39,173
Regardless of what people think⸺

622
00:37:39,966 --> 00:37:45,846
I tried to stick to the method I believed in and cherish the taste of this restaurant.

623
00:37:46,681 --> 00:37:51,602
That was Kazuki's shogi style.

624
00:37:54,814 --> 00:37:56,440
big brother

625
00:37:57,858 --> 00:38:00,861
Won't you come back to my house?

626
00:38:04,824 --> 00:38:07,785
Dad and I will make the sweets⸺

627
00:38:08,536 --> 00:38:12,123
Brother, all you have to do is deliver that to as many people as possible.

628
00:38:14,166 --> 00:38:16,669
Because he's a professional in that field.

629
00:38:31,183 --> 00:38:32,309
father

630
00:38:34,854 --> 00:38:36,147
no…

631
00:38:36,939 --> 00:38:38,149
master

632
00:38:41,694 --> 00:38:43,446
It's been bad so far

633
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:52,705
Can you leave the sales of this store to me?

634
00:38:56,542 --> 00:38:58,502
In addition to the previous flavors of Gankoan⸺

635
00:38:58,586 --> 00:39:01,839
I also have an idea for a new Japanese confectionery exclusively for mail order.

636
00:39:03,466 --> 00:39:06,469
If my father doesn't mind, he won't make it for me...

637
00:39:14,060 --> 00:39:15,227
father!

638
00:39:17,188 --> 00:39:19,565
(Kumakura) I make sweets because I am a craftsman.

639
00:39:20,232 --> 00:39:22,026
What else can you do?

640
00:39:24,403 --> 00:39:27,281
If you want me to make something, come to the workshop.

641
00:39:33,162 --> 00:39:34,413
big brother

642
00:39:48,385 --> 00:39:50,346
thank you

643
00:40:07,571 --> 00:40:11,909
I feel like Ryuumi-sensei saved me.

644
00:40:11,992 --> 00:40:15,538
(Tatsumi) Yeah? What did you do?

645
00:40:19,792 --> 00:40:21,502
Words to Kazuki⸺

646
00:40:23,754 --> 00:40:26,090
You said it to me, right?

647
00:40:31,303 --> 00:40:33,389
I have to surpass my father⸺

648
00:40:34,557 --> 00:40:37,768
Even for me, who was addicted to invisible pressure⸺

649
00:40:38,269 --> 00:40:39,645
It stings

650
00:40:40,396 --> 00:40:45,901
(Tatsumi) Hmm...I'm like that.

651
00:40:45,985 --> 00:40:49,738
Um... I didn't mean to do anything clever.

652
00:40:56,662 --> 00:40:59,039
To exceed or not to exceed⸺

653
00:41:00,166 --> 00:41:02,751
Don't worry about whether it will turn out or not⸺

654
00:41:02,835 --> 00:41:06,505
I just want to become a lawyer that I can trust.

655
00:41:09,049 --> 00:41:13,679
That's my style of chess⸺

656
00:41:14,805 --> 00:41:16,432
I think I understand

657
00:41:20,186 --> 00:41:23,564
That's why I'm so grateful that Ryumi-sensei is here...

658
00:41:26,483 --> 00:41:29,361
Huh? What, lie again?

659
00:41:30,571 --> 00:41:32,573
♪～

660
00:41:32,740 --> 00:41:34,116
(Toshie) Mr. Yojiro⸺

661
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:36,827
Until Kotaro-kun becomes a full-fledged adult⸺

662
00:41:36,911 --> 00:41:39,538
Please wait just a little longer.

663
00:41:44,001 --> 00:41:45,169
 (sound of tapping on table)

664
00:41:45,252 --> 00:41:47,129
(Tatsuo) Last time he was given a suspended sentence⸺

665
00:41:47,213 --> 00:41:48,923
To think that he would re-offend without any delay⸺

666
00:41:49,006 --> 00:41:51,759
This time, we have to punish him with a prison sentence...

667
00:41:51,842 --> 00:41:54,136
(Kasumi) Okay, thank you for your hard work.

668
00:41:54,220 --> 00:41:56,347
Mr. Kotaro, you haven't drank at all yet, have you?

669
00:41:56,430 --> 00:41:57,598
- (Kasumi) If you don't mind- (Torataro) Ah...

670
00:41:57,681 --> 00:41:58,974
Thank you

671
00:42:02,269 --> 00:42:04,688
Oh, uh... the other day⸺

672
00:42:04,772 --> 00:42:07,107
I was talking to Ryumi-sensei...

673
00:42:07,191 --> 00:42:12,029
But I had one best friend.

674
00:42:15,449 --> 00:42:17,076
But I am⸺

675
00:42:18,911 --> 00:42:21,080
I lost that person

676
00:42:23,457 --> 00:42:24,708
At shogi

677
00:42:27,545 --> 00:42:28,796
I see.

678
00:42:30,714 --> 00:42:34,134
About Tatsumi Towa-chan⸺

679
00:42:34,218 --> 00:42:36,262
I'm still dragging it after all

680
00:42:37,930 --> 00:42:41,183
Is that person Ryumi-sensei's best friend?

681
00:42:41,767 --> 00:42:42,810
Yeah

682
00:42:43,894 --> 00:42:46,563
Komaki (Komaki) Go to Uba⸺

683
00:42:46,647 --> 00:42:49,525
Tatsumi and I were at the same time at the encouragement meeting.

684
00:42:49,608 --> 00:42:52,570
She was three years older than me.

685
00:42:52,653 --> 00:42:54,071
My best friend⸺

686
00:42:54,154 --> 00:42:56,490
He was also a good rival.

687
00:42:59,743 --> 00:43:02,579
What do you mean by losing in shogi?

688
00:43:04,123 --> 00:43:05,916
To be precise...

689
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:07,376
～♪

690
00:43:07,459 --> 00:43:12,381
Tatsumi stole the shogi from her.

691
00:43:18,470 --> 00:43:19,972
Is the will a chess game?

692
00:43:20,055 --> 00:43:21,807
 (Tatsumi) This is a project for me.

693
00:43:21,890 --> 00:43:22,808
 (Kirie) It really is a will⸺

694
00:43:22,891 --> 00:43:23,726
Is it possible to say?

695
00:43:23,809 --> 00:43:25,144
 (Shiori) Change your eye color like that...

696
00:43:25,227 --> 00:43:26,145
(Tatsumi) Someone gets hurt⸺

697
00:43:26,228 --> 00:43:27,062
I don't want to see it anymore

698
00:43:27,146 --> 00:43:28,856
 Use this Tsume Shogi to divide your inheritance⸺

699
00:43:28,939 --> 00:43:29,898
After solving

700
00:43:29,982 --> 00:43:31,233
(Usagiba) It’s been a while.

701
00:43:31,317 --> 00:43:32,901
Usa-chan?
